This hipster cafe is definitely Instagram-worthy, and I love it! The place is quite small, but the interior is really cute and they have free wifi. It's a great place to just enjoy your coffee with friends or to get some work done if you can find yourself a table.
They always get my order wrong. I don't feel they really pay me as a customer any attention when I order. I have been there 5 times and 3ctines my order was wrong.

Unlike many Dunkin locations this one did not burn the espresso in my macchiato this morning so my drink was delicious this morning which I was happy about. My only complaint is that they mislabeled my coffee as original when it should have been decaf, so I had to go back around and wait in the line all over again to tell them of the error and get a replacement but when we finally got to the window the girl said she definitely made it decaf it was just mislabeled on the cup... So it was a big waste of time for (hopefully) nothing, but I'm not even sure I trust that it's decaf... So that was really frustrating. Please take better care to properly label drinks because people like me who need to avoid caffeine really depend on that label being accurate!
